The MrScraper MCP server allows AI agents to perform web scraping and structured data extraction through a cloud-hosted interface [1]. It uses the Model Context Protocol’s HTTP transport to connect directly to MrScraper’s engine, avoiding the need for local installation [1][2].

To integrate the server, add the following configuration to your MCP host [1]:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "mrscraper": {
      "type": "http",
      "url": "https://mcp.mrscraper.com/mcp",
      "headers": {
        "Authorization": "Bearer <MRSCRAPER_API_TOKEN>"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

The server exposes tools such as create_scraper and rerun_ai_scraper, enabling agents to intelligently extract data from websites [1]. This setup provides a secure, scalable way to manage scraping workflows without infrastructure management [1].
